Subject: Re: NT versus Linux
Date: Fri, 20 Aug 1993 16:34:20 GMT

In article <930819201354.23155@world> brileary@world.std.com (Brian Leary) writes:
>Angry that after all the gloat about how lean and mean linux is, NT's
>kernel is less one fifth that size? Tough! Or that your file system

But what is it (the microkernel itself, the 50K one you're so proud of)
capable of doing?  Remember, to keep it that size you have to make sure it
doesn't load any of the installable drivers/modules --- otherwise it's not a
fair comparison, because the actual working size of the kernel will be the
size of the microkernel plus the automatically-loaded drivers.

Which is why we're responding to you:  you appear not to have the faintest
clue even about NT.  If you're the best NT can do for advocacy, it's dead
already (but luckily for NT, Gates is only unethical, not stupid).

